value.value: An interleukin-1 receptor-associated kinase 1 that is a translation product of some mRNA whose exon structure and start site selection renders it capable of giving rise to a protein with the amino acid sequence represented by UniProtKB:P51617-1 or a 1:1 ortholog thereof.

label.value: interleukin-1 receptor-associated kinase 1 isoform 1 unmodified form

value.value: An interleukin-1 receptor-associated kinase 1 isoform 1 that has not been subjected to any co- or post-translational residue modification or peptide bond cleavage.

An interleukin-1 receptor-associated kinase 1 isoform 1 phosphorylated form in which the phosphorylation by interleukin-1 receptor-associated kinase 4 (IRAK-4) occurs on the conserved Thr residue (Thr-209 in human) located at the N terminus of the kinase domain. This is the first step following the activation of the TLR/IL-1 receptor complex. This phosphorylation results in a conformational change of the kinase domain. Example: UniProtKB:P51617-1, Thr-209, MOD:00047.

An interleukin-1 receptor-associated kinase 1 isoform 1 phosphorylated form in which the phosphorylation by interleukin-1 receptor-associated kinase 4 (IRAK-4) occurs on the conserved Thr residue (Thr-209 in human) located near the N terminus of the kinase domain, and on a Thr residue located in the activation loop (Thr-387 in human). The latter phosphorylation is the second step following the activation of the TLR/IL-1 receptor complex. Example: UniProtKB:P51617-1, Thr-209/Thr-387, MOD:00047.

An interleukin-1 receptor-associated kinase 1 isoform 1 phosphorylated form in which the phosphorylation occurs by interleukin-1 receptor-associated kinase 4 (IRAK-4) and extensively autophosphorylated in the Pro-, Ser-, and Thr-rich ProST region between the N-terminal death domain and kinase domain. Example: UniProtKB:P51617-1, Thr-209/Thr-387, MOD:00047|MOD:00046.

label.value: dual specificity mitogen-activated protein kinase kinase 6 isoform 1

value.value: A dual specificity mitogen-activated protein kinase kinase 6 that is a translation product of some mRNA whose exon structure and start site selection renders it capable of giving rise to a protein with the amino acid sequence represented by UniProtKB:P52564-1 or a 1:1 ortholog thereof.

label.value: dual specificity mitogen-activated protein kinase kinase 6 isoform 1 unmodified form

value.value: A dual specificity mitogen-activated protein kinase kinase 6 isoform 1 that has not been subjected to any co- or post-translational residue modification or peptide bond cleavage.

label.value: dual specificity mitogen-activated protein kinase kinase 6 isoform 1 phosphorylated 1

value.value: A dual specificity mitogen-activated protein kinase kinase 6 isoform 1 phosphorylated form in which the phosphorylation occurs in the activation loop by ubiquitinated TAK1. Example: UniProtKB:P52564-1, Ser-207, MOD:00046|Thr-211, MOD:00047.
A mitogen-activated protein kinase 8 phosphorylated form in which the phosphorylation occurs at the TxY motif that activates the MAP kinases.

label.value: cereal lectin with Chitin recognition protein domains

value.value: A protein that contains four copies of the Chitin recognition protein (Pfam:PF00187) domain and is 190-220 residues long.
A cereal lectin with Chitin recognition protein domains that is a translation product of the wheat WGA1 gene or a 1:1 ortholog thereof.
A cereal lectin with Chitin recognition protein domains that is a translation product of the wheat WGA3 gene or a 1:1 ortholog thereof.
A protein that is a standalone version of the Legume lectin domain (Pfam:PF00139), and is approximately 250-300 residues long.

label.value: leucoagglutinating phytohemagglutinin isoform 1, signal peptide removed glycosylated form

value.value: A leucoagglutinating phytohemagglutinin isoform 1, signal peptide removed form that includes at least one glycosylated residue.

label.value: dual specificity mitogen-activated protein kinase kinase 3/6

value.value: A protein that is a gene product level of the MAP2K3 or the MAP2K6 gene. Members of this class activate phosphorylation of a threonine and a tyrosine residue in MAP kinase p38 exclusively.

label.value: dual specificity mitogen-activated protein kinase kinase 3 isoform 2 phosphorylated form

value.value: A dual specificity mitogen-activated protein kinase kinase 3 isoform 2 that includes at least one phosphorylated residue.

label.value: dual specificity mitogen-activated protein kinase kinase 6 isoform 1 phosphorylated form

value.value: A dual specificity mitogen-activated protein kinase kinase 6 isoform 1 that includes at least one phosphorylated residue.
A mitogen-activated protein kinase 8 that includes at least one phosphorylated residue.

label.value: agglutinin isolectin 2 isoform 1 cleaved and pyrrolidone carboxylic acid modified form

value.value: An agglutinin isolectin 2 isoform 1, signal peptide removed form that has had the propeptide removed and post-translationally modified to include a pyrrolidone carboxylic acid.

label.value: dual specificity mitogen-activated protein kinase kinase 4 phosphorylated form

value.value: A dual specificity mitogen-activated protein kinase kinase 4 that includes at least one phosphorylated residue.

label.value: dual specificity mitogen-activated protein kinase kinase 4 phosphorylated 1

value.value: A dual specificity mitogen-activated protein kinase kinase 4 phosphorylated form in which the phosphorylation occurs on Ser/Thr residues within the activation loop by MAP kinase kinase kinases.
A protein that is a tyrosine kinase receptor that is activated by dimerization, resulting in autophosphorylation of intracellular tyrosine residues and triggering of the signal transduction cascade.

A protein that is a neurotrophic polypeptide factor that regulates neuronal differentiation and is essential for neuronal survival, neurite growth and plasticity. It contains a signal peptide, a propeptide, and a C-terminal Nerve growth factor family (Pfam:PF00243) domain.

A protein that contains multiple TNFR/NGFR cysteine-rich region (Pfam:PF00020) within the extracellular ligand-binding domain, a type I (single pass) transmembrane domain, and a cytoplasmic Death domain (Pfam:PF00531) required for intracellular signaling.
A protein that is a plant-specific oxidoreductase containing a signal peptide and one copy of the Peroxidase (Pfam:PF00141) domain.

A protein that was initially identified as an antibacterial enzyme located in egg whites of Embden goose, but is now known to exist in both mammals and fish. Lysozyme catalyzes hydrolysis of most bacterial cell walls by cleaving the beta-1,4 glycosidic bond between N-acetyl-d-glucosamine (NAG) and N-acetylmuramic acid (NAM) in the peptidoglycan layer. It contains one copy of the Transglycosylase SLT domain (Pfam:PF01464).
A coagulase that has had the signal peptide removed.

A bone marrow proteoglycan that is a translation product of some mRNA whose exon structure and start site selection renders it capable of giving rise to a protein with the amino acid sequence represented by UniProtKB:P13727-1 or a 1:1 ortholog thereof.
A bone marrow proteoglycan isoform 1, signal peptide removed form that has had the acidic propeptide removed.

A protein that is a glycohydrolytic enzyme, which removes sialic acid residues from a variety of sialoglycoconjugates. Sialidases have highly conserved active site residues, the F/YRIV/P motif in the N-terminal part and the Asp boxes (consensus S/TXD(x)GxTW/F present as three to five repeat in the protein) similar to their viral and bacterial counter parts.

A retinoic acid receptor alpha that is a translation product of some mRNA whose exon structure and start site selection renders it capable of giving rise to a protein with the amino acid sequence represented by UniProtKB:P11416-1 or a 1:1 ortholog thereof.

A retinoic acid receptor alpha that is a translation product of some mRNA whose exon structure and start site selection renders it capable of giving rise to a protein with the amino acid sequence represented by UniProtKB:P11416-2 or a 1:1 ortholog thereof. This isoform lacks the N-terminal region that is known to be important for trans-activation by other members of the nuclear receptor superfamily.

A nucleolar transcription factor 1 that is a translation product of some mRNA whose exon structure and start site selection renders it capable of giving rise to a protein with the amino acid sequence represented by UniProtKB:P25976-1 or a 1:1 ortholog thereof.

A nucleolar transcription factor 1 that is a translation product of some mRNA whose exon structure and start site selection renders it capable of giving rise to a protein with the amino acid sequence represented by UniProtKB:P25976-2 or a 1:1 ortholog thereof.

A sphingolipid Delta(4)-desaturase/C4-monooxygenase DES2 that is a translation product of some mRNA whose exon structure and start site selection renders it capable of giving rise to a protein with the amino acid sequence represented by UniProtKB:Q8R2F2-1 or a 1:1 ortholog thereof.

A sphingolipid Delta(4)-desaturase/C4-monooxygenase DES2 that is a translation product of some mRNA whose exon structure and start site selection renders it capable of giving rise to a protein with the amino acid sequence represented by UniProtKB:Q8R2F2-2 or a 1:1 ortholog thereof. This isoform has a shorter C-terminal sequence as compared to isoform 1.
